channel.title: [RSPS] Main- developer, experienced coders needed! [RSPS]
channel.description:
[size=18pt]ADRIAN CHRIS[/size]
Blablabla, if you're an experienced coder just contact me on msn: Avocadoftw@hotmail.com Me and another guy have a source, and we have we been working on it recently. We have experience, but we still have a lack of knowledge and we really need a MAIN DEVELOPER. Contact me as soon as possible, and only if you're interested. You HAVE to be motivated, and you have to want to make a new Rsps that will be among the top servers in the future. You have my word, it will be among the top servers. EDIT: I DON'T NEED TO ADD PICTURES OR ANYTHING TO PROVE THAT THIS DEVELOPMENT TEAM WILL BE SUCCESSFUL. READ, ADD ME, THEN TALK AND FIND OUT YOURSELF. Let me remind you of this: We WILL be SUCCESSFUL. MSN: Avocadoftw@hotmail.com
Recently I decided to start my own project on making a new Rsps. The only problem that prevents me from doing this: I am very new to coding. I think it's fun getting known with coding, but I still have a long way to go, though I seem to learn pretty fast from what I have taken a look at so far. As I am writing this, I am completely aware of that it might seem stupid to the more experienced coders who take a look at this thread in the future, that I started this project with my lack of knowledge. The thing is: it is not stupid at all. I have played Runescape Private Servers for years, and RuneScape before that. I also have a very good experience with communities, and I know very well of the difference between what's right and wrong. Life is unfair, but I believe in the best of it. For as long as I have played RSPS's, I always meant that I'd fit in as an owner, or atleast part of the Staff. I never applied for Staff in any Rsps's though, even if I had the possibilites. The more experienced you are as an coder, the better. When it comes to Staffpositions, I can only say that I am looking for experienced people who are able to put some effort to the server. This means you will have to put some effort and give me a good impression of what you are capable of. If I am hosting a server, I am NOT adding random people to Staff. You have to deserve it. Be aware of this before you decide to be a part of this server, which WILL be on the toplists in the future. You have my word on it, all we need is patience. That is why we do this for fun.
The Server: Well, what can I say? I have no idea of what the name should be. I have thought of many ideas, but they are all trash. I want something creative and original, and rather not something with "SCAPE" in it as of that it's sexually abused by all kind of RSPS's. I don't mind any 600 Servers with HD graphics, but I rather have the old school 317 Grahpics with the following features.
Features: Gear: All spirit shields 100% Dragon claws 100% Staff of Light 100% Korasi 100% All Chaotics 100% All Godswords 100% All PvP Armour 100% Torva, Pernix, Virtus 100%
Ancient curses! No dupes! Stable economy! Proper item switching! Edgeville as Home (Donators features- to be discussed, not sure) Automatic donation! (Working Duel Arena?) All skills 100% (Summoning, hunter, dungeoneering, construction- not needed) PvP zones- PvP drops (Statius, Vestas... Corrupt, non- corrupt) Ancient magics Lunar magics Teleporters
Warriors Guild Barrows JAD 100% Corp 100% Nex 100% Tormented Demons 100% KBD 100% Steel Dragons, Iron dragons Mithril Dragons 100% (placed in deep wildy, a bit overpowered, drops Korasi and Staff of light?) Full GWD (With killcount, not being able to noclip into chambers) And more...!
I will be the Owner. The most experienced coder will be an Owner next to me. I am not sure how I will choose my Staff list and it's positions yet (that's not the point of making the server and shouldn't matter too much), but I am looking for three experienced coders! Donations will be sent to the Server's Paypal address. I will have access to the PayPal address at first. (Money will be spent on vBulletin, Dedicated Servers, Advertising, more..) You have to be motivated for this if you want to join. With the features I have listed above, we can make it far. There will be a lot of work, and it's going to take AWHILE. We'll never give up. Life will be a first priority, but when we are able to we will try to make progress. IF YOU ARE INTERESTED, ADD ME ON MSN: Avocadoftw@hotmail.com
Also, leave a reply below!
Development Team Applications, 2012 A. Real Life Details 1) Name (Optional)- 2) Age- 3) Timezone- 4) Country of Residence- 5) Languages spoken- 6) Estimated time you're able to work with the Development Team a week- 7) Estimated time you're able to work with the Development Team a holday week-
B. Personal Character and Personality Hobbies and interests 1) Tell us some of your hobbies in a detailed paragraph or two- 2) What are you interested in- 3) Desired Career when you are an adult (Put N/A if you are undecided) 4) Write a one paragraph mini essay about your unique personalities- 5) Rare your maturity on a 1-10 scale with 1 being very immature and 10 being very mature- a) Why do you rate yourself what you rate yourself- b) How can you improve your maturity-
C. Ingame powers, ranks 1. Why do you want to be ranked at the forums/ingame- 2. We will develop a relationship, and within a period of time I will know if you're trusted or not. Yet, how can I trust you? 3. How can you provide any help to help me as an owner?
Essays (you will have to answer both of the following tasks before you deliver your application). 1. Imagine your about to start a server.You finally get it to run and three months later, your peaking 250 players. You will need a gameplan on how you will run the server, choose your staff, and go about managing the server with a high population.Explain to me in a 2-3 paragraph essay how you will do these things.Include clear and detailed examples. 2. Explain to me in a 2-3 paragraph essay why you choose to become a potential Server Moderator/Administrator in truth and honesty.
